!! Creating a New Agent

# In the agent workspace, click the "+" new tab button
# Click "Create New Agent"
# Complete the three-step wizard:

!!! Step 1: Set Up Agent

* Select a template from the search box (built-in, plugin, or cloud templates available)
* Enter a name for the agent, e.g. "Code Assistant"

!!! Step 2: Edit Prompt

* Expand the prompt configuration form and switch to the relevant tab
* Expand the array item and edit the system prompt text field
* This becomes the default prompt for the agent

!!! Step 3: Test and Use

* Send a test message in the preview chat to verify the behavior
* Click "Save and Use Agent" to create and immediately start a new conversation

!! Editing an Existing Agent

Click the agent settings button in the top-right corner of any conversation tab to modify the prompt for that conversation. To make a permanent change, edit the agent definition directly in the agent workspace.
